response.original_title: Landlocked: The Story of the Freshwater Striped Bass
response.overview: When South Carolina closed its dams the striped bass origanally an ocean fish became landlocked and unable to go to saltwater. After several years, fishermen and biologists realized the fish were thriving and reproducing incredibly for the first time ever in freshwater.
response.title: Landlocked: The Story of the Freshwater Striped Bass
